<paragraph id="267EE698E68483616B4C514301868B60" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="236AB172FA862A973743919331C22130" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Holotype, female, 5 mm (with oostegite buds), USNM 282716. Paratypes: 1 male, 5.4 mm, USNM 282717; 1 male AM P.45339.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6CB5F5E764486488F3AAE0838E2FED71" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="type locality">
<paragraph id="193D8833C8C1AC129D35E6DA347F0E6B" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C1424C31F3BC7D3016E1035E33922D4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Gulf of Mexico, south of Mobile Bay (approximately 
<geoCoordinate id="0C5A8ECF56308CF8E7C2BC2AF51D5751" degrees="29" direction="north" minutes="12" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="29.2">29°12'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="BBF8C8FF1C3A18DCA849FD0579D64AB4" degrees="85" direction="west" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-85.11667">85°07'W</geoCoordinate>
), from stomach of a Blackfin grenadier, 
<taxonomicName id="975EBCA6264E735FD8C5C3A4A9AC11FB" baseAuthorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Coelorinchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coelorinchus caribbaeus" order="Gadiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caribbaeus">
<emphasis id="745598238B6489DD955511652292D325" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Coelorinchus caribbaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Goode &amp; Bean, 1885), 200 m depth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1AD4112D64A3D1D72ACD72D263CFB65" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="depth range">
<paragraph id="1387E68A10C0ADC1067C674D61908610" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Depth range.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBD0E539B777259E2C06B86C402F0CF4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
95-200 m (
<bibRefCitation id="C389111805C9AE97FAB0B1632C014A11" author="Lowry, JK" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 148" refId="B129" refString="Lowry, JK, Stoddart, HE, 1997. Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae. Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises 10: 1 - 148" title="Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae." volume="10" year="1997">Lowry and Stoddart 1997</bibRefCitation>
). The deeper record represents animals taken from fish stomachs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FF2751060C36A7C30624F88D91172C3A" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="05550D637CDEDBD22B816730815E7AEA" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5B429E0BD723D24929A897072CF83D4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="67D043DF9F202AF48C9CEEA1BEA95125" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Argentina</emphasis>
: east of 
<normalizedToken id="E4D4AE0B32D2B0AD5723159E727DA1B0" originalValue="Bahía">Bahia</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="6370C3F45FB56C80AD72D54D558895C8" originalValue="Unión">Union</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1EBE0DEAEB3E741E11ADE130FAAA0CBA" author="Lowry, JK" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 148" refId="B129" refString="Lowry, JK, Stoddart, HE, 1997. Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae. Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises 10: 1 - 148" title="Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae." volume="10" year="1997">Lowry and Stoddart 1997</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="FA09680649B3857F7F511885BF57C1B9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">United States</emphasis>
: Gulf of Mexico, south of Mobile Bay and south-east of the Mississippi River Delta (
<bibRefCitation id="60F743F0E45B52D9E1AC1A89F0C5A34F" author="Lowry, JK" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 148" refId="B129" refString="Lowry, JK, Stoddart, HE, 1997. Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae. Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises 10: 1 - 148" title="Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae." volume="10" year="1997">Lowry and Stoddart 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
