<subSubSection id="36A00D8C9B7EAC0250BFC938078F4212" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="BCC2A30CC2D35C7186F634D18FD7166C" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6935C3A5E6C958E2A17FBFA3D1EE8092" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Known from sandy bottoms, but also a scavenger by implication (
<bibRefCitation id="A5C2DB778439C16BB80A452A38A4F815" author="Lowry, JK" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 148" refId="B129" refString="Lowry, JK, Stoddart, HE, 1997. Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae. Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises 10: 1 - 148" title="Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae." volume="10" year="1997">Lowry and Stoddart 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0EB24E97861A477E3D8F484B0B3B3C94" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DB992B68AE29E7D194D1DA744FED6816" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="45E09CB0D06D5596BF0016EE4888BBF4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
This species was described from three specimens: two from fish stomachs in the Gulf of Mexico and in the collections of the USNM, and another specimen taken in a trawl off Argentina by the USS 
<emphasis id="F9C96F2A0A9158D10A3DB8D500456DC7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Albatross</emphasis>
in the collections of the AM. No new material has been recorded in the literature since its description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
